    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated basa</strong> and cook on a high heat for 3-4 min on each side until golden and cooked through</p><p>Once cooked transfer the <strong>basa</strong> to a plate, cover loosely with<strong> tin foil</strong> and set aside</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
